In fact, I'd say it's in your best interest to work things out so you can do whatever you want with Voreverl's body. Hers is of no concern to me. But--" Horatius spits out the words-- "Bern is someone I have known for many more precious years than you. That man is the reason I'm alive today, the reason for my existence. And you say *you're* the one who *needs* that body? You wouldn't know 'need' if it struck you in the face. No, that body belongs to me and no one else-- he is *mine*. You're just another thief trying to steal him away from me, just like that bitch. Indeed, we will have to work this out." After a brief pause, they remember the other subject of conversation. *“…”* The line is silent for a bit.

*”It’s like that, huh? I’m sorry, this is embarrassing. I’m still in maternal mode.”*

She clears her throat.

*”Get over yourself, you stupid fucking kid. You think you have possession over this guy? The only proof of that in this world is power. And you’re not even here. I waited twenty fucking years. And my personal destiny, wyrd, throws the perfect opportunity my way. Do you have any idea what that’s like? How—Of course you wouldn’t know. You’re not just a child. You’re a boy, right? A woman who wants success has to steal it. And I will. I’ll let Intuition take the power gap I create. And with his good graces, who knows? Whole world will be open for me. The important part is that you aren’t even in this scheme. I don’t need you. But you keep your damn mouth shut and you’ll live to see it. Capisce?”*

Horatius laughs. "Yeah, there's no way you'd have taken that lying down, heh. 'A woman who wants success has to steal it'... I couldn't have put it better myself. And wow-- twenty years! Your drive and dedication are nothing short of admirable." Their laughter trails off, and their voice turns cold as well. "I'm sorry, though. That dedication won't get you anywhere without the ingenuity to back it up. No, the very fact that you think me a boy proves it! I've never had *destiny* on my side, yet I accomplished in ten years what you couldn't in *twice* that time. All I'm trying to get across is... from one success thief to another, I may not have even registered on your radar until now, but you know how the saying goes. Don't count your chickens before they hatch."
